 @dante19890  it's not about being able to play at that resolution, it's about checking the performance of the card at that resolution with native rendering. 

If you go back to how we tested GPU's in the early 2000's it was always tested at resolutions that no one would play at to see how far technology has come and the improvements over the previous generations. 

If we really go into "Playability" of games, well most gamers tweak the settings to get the best visuals and perfromance at a specific resolution which is nigh impoosible to benchmark. Hence seeing the performance at native 4k makes sense to see how much headroom you need to make and how much tech has imrpoved espeically when it comes to RT and  PT.

